review.description: A charming gem of a restaurant with delicious food and lovely view of the area. I had hummus and couscous dish which their home made spicy sauce. Perfectly paired with a summer book and a peaceful setting. Will be back for more!
review.author: Yana R.

review.description: Very sweet corner cafe. Espresso and variants for coffee. Tea. Good breakfast. We shared (1) baked eggs and salmon and (2) an orange blossom waffle. Both were quite tasty. Service was warm, if not particularly quick. "Warm vibe/good food" is how I'd sum it up.
review.author: Malabar J.

review.description: Great breakfast and lunch options; I've had the baked egg sandwich with sausage and the veggie burger both of which were excellent. They also have a great selection of teas, with the Du Hammam being quite refreshing. A bit of a walk from the nearest subway, but well worth it
review.author: Patrick C.

review.description: Oh. My. God.  Delicious breakfast in a super cool spot.  The neighborhood has been waiting for another (VHH fits the mold) chill, interesting and great place, and now we've got it!  I'm already looking forward to going back...
review.author: Jeffrey K.
